        <h3 style="padding: 0px; font-size: 18px;" >Instructions</h3>
        <div class="instructions">
            Use this to export text documents from Indaba.
            <br><br>
            In step one, you will chose a type of document (a "product") from a list. You must pick a product with at least one completed document.
            <br><br>
            In step two you will chose specific iterations of the document (a "target") to export. You can filter the list by tags; this allows the selection of regional groups. You can select all to get the entire list.
            <br><br>
            In step three, you will download a ZIP file. The ZIP will contain a set of TXT files and CSV files. The TXT files are the content you want (in plaintext with HTML markup included). The CSV files provide some metadata for the TXT files, such as the author and creation date. 
        </div>
    </div>
</div>